Interface Builder<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of object to build
All Known Subinterfaces:
OSCommandBuilder<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AppleScriptBuilder, ConfigurationBuilder, FactoryBasedCommandBuilder, NamedBuilder
public interface Builder<T>

Builds an object of type T. A builder typically provides methods by which callers can supply configuration parameters for the object to be built. When a caller calls build(), the builder creates a new object based on the accumulated configuration parameters.
